article.description: Jarelle Reischel had 19 points, seven rebounds, five assists and five steals to help Eastern Kentucky beat Florida Atlantic 80-73 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Eastern Kentucky holds on to beat Florida Atlantic 80-73
article.linkText: Eastern Kentucky holds on to beat Florida Atlantic 80-73
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. -- Jarelle Reischel had 19 points, seven rebounds, five assists and five steals to help Eastern Kentucky beat Florida Atlantic 80-73 on Tuesday night. Reischel was 9 of 9 from the stripe, including two to seal it with 28 seconds left. Eastern Kentucky opened the second half on a 12-3 run, with seven points from JaVontae Hawkins, for a 49-38 lead. The spurt was highlighted by Nick Mayo's steal and feed to Hawkins for an alley-oop dunk. Florida Atlantic rallied to within 68-66 but EKU answered with a 6-0 run, capped by Dujuanta Weaver's athletic tip-in of Reischel's missed 3-pointer. Hawkins made it a seven-point game with a minute left on a putback of his own miss. Mayo added 18 points for Eastern Kentucky (8-4) and Hawkins finished with 15. Adonis Filer led Florida Atlantic (2-7) with 16 points and Ronald Delph, a 7-footer from Auburn, added 11 in his first game.
